    "Hawaii Civil Rights Protection Act",
    "Relief"
  ],
  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "description",
      "abstract": "Establishes a civil cause of action for interference with constitutional and statutory rights through threats, intimidation, or coercion.  Authorizes private rights of action.  Authorizes actions to be brought by the Attorney General, County Corporation Counsel, or County Attorney.  Authorizes injunctive relief, declaratory relief, and certain monetary relief.  Includes protections for constitutionally protected speech.  Effective 7/1/3000.  (HD1)"
    }
  ],
